          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1708419853988-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Remove from the heat, add your <strong>prawn gyozas</strong> and carefully add a splash of <strong>cold water</strong>, return to the heat and cook, covered, for 5 min, then remove the lid, and cook for a further 5-7 min or until golden and crispy</p><p>Tip: Be careful when adding the water to the pan, it may splash!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1708419872562-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1708419872562-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1708419872562-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1708419872562-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1708419872562-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, add the<strong> cooled rice</strong> and your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and cook for 2-3 min until everything is combined</p><p>Once combined, push the rice to one side of the pan and crack your <strong>egg[s] </strong>into the other side</p><p>Stir the egg[s] with a wooden spoon to break the yolk[s] and cook for 1-2 min until it resembles scrambled egg, then mix it all through the rice – this is your <strong>yakimeshi egg fried rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1708419910465-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1708419910465-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1708419910465-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1708419910465-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1708419910465-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and the <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>in a bowl – this is your <strong>chilli & garlic dipping sauce</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1708419921324-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1708419921324-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1708419921324-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1708419921324-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1708419921324-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy prawn gyozas </strong>and <strong>yakimeshi egg fried rice </strong>with the <strong>chilli & garlic dipping sauce </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining shichimi togarashi </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
